obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (8341)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8341&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the State`
  line `Emblem of India (Prohibition of Improper Use) Act, 2005.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India, and also applies to citizens of India out side India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 12th September, 2007, vide notification No. S.O. 1526(E) dated 12th September, 2007, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II sec.3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (8342)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8342&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "competent authority" means any authority competent under any law for the time being in`
  line `force to register any company, firm, other body of persons or any trade mark or design or to grant a`
  line patent;
  line
  line `(b) "emblem" means the State Emblem of India as described and specified in the Schedule to be`
  line `used as an official seal of the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (8343)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition of improper use of emblem.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8343&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, no person shall use the emblem or any colourable imitation thereof in any`
  line `manner which tends to create an impression that it relates to the Government or that it is an official`
  line `document of the Central Government, or as the case may be, the State Government, without the previous`
  line `permission of the Central Government or of such officer of that Government as may be authorised by it in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, "person" includes a former functionary of the Central`
  line `Government or the State Governments.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (8344)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of use of emblem for wrongful gain.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8344&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No person shall use the emblem for the`
  line `purpose of any trade, business, calling or profession or in the title of any patent, or in any trade mark or`
  line `design, except in such cases and under such conditions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (8345)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of registration of certain companies, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8345&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force, no competent authority shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) register a trade mark or design which bears the emblem, or`
  line
  line `(b) grant patent in respect of an invention which bears a title containing the emblem.`
  line
  line `(2) If any question arises before a competent authority whether any emblem is an emblem specified in`
  line `the Schedule or a colourable imitation thereof, the competent authority shall refer the question to the`
  line `Central Government and the decision of the Central Government thereon shall be final`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (8346)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `General powers of Central Government to regulate use of emblem.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8346&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may make such provision by rules as appears to it to be necessary, to regulate the use of the`
  line `emblem in official seal that is used in offices of the Central Government and the State Governments and`
  line `their organisations including diplomatic missions abroad, subject to such restrictions and conditions as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government shall have powers—`
  line
  line `(a) to notify the use of emblem on stationery, the method of printing or embossing it on demiofficial`
  line `stationery by the constitutional authorities, Ministers, Members of Parliament, Members of`
  line `Legislative Assemblies, officers of the Central Government and the State Governments;`
  line
  line `(b) to specify the design of the official seal consisting of the emblem;`
  line
  line `(c) to restrict the display of emblem on vehicles of constitutional authorities, foreign dignitaries,`
  line `Ministers of the Central Government and the State Governments;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide for guidelines for display of emblem on public buildings in India, the diplomatic`
  line `missions and on the buildings occupied by India's consulatesa broad;`
  line
  line `(e) to specify conditions for the use of emblem for various other purposes including the use for`
  line `educational purposes and the armed forces personnel;`
  line
  line `(f) to do all such things (including the specification of design of the emblem and its use in the`
  line `manner whatsoever) as the Central Government considers necessary or expedient for the exercise of`
  line `the foregoing powers.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (8347)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8347&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who contravenes the provisions of section 3 shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to five thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both, or if having been previously convicted of an offence under this section, is again`
  line `convicted of any such offence, he shall be punishable for the second and for every subsequent offence`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months, which may extend to two years and`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of section 4 for any wrongful gain shall be punishable`
  line `for such offence with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months, which may extend`
  line `to two years and with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (8348)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Previous sanction for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8348&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for any offence punishable under this Act`
  line `shall be instituted, except with the previous sanction of the Central Government or of any officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf by general or special order of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (8349)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8349&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall exempt any person from any suit or other proceedings which`
  line `might be brought against him under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (8350)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8350&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act or any rule made thereunder shall`
  line `have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other enactment or`
  line `instrument having effect by virtue of such enactment.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (8351)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011&sectionId=8351&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00052_200550_1517807327011
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) cases and conditions regulating the use of emblem under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) making rules to regulate the use of the emblem in official seal of the Government and`
  line `specifying restrictions and conditions relating thereto under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the use of emblem on stationery, design of official seal consisting of emblem and other`
  line `matters under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) authorising officer by general or special order for giving previous sanction for instituting`
  line `prosecution under section 8; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediatelyfollowing the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both House agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
